            <p id="desc">When the state of the local audio stream changes (including the state of
                the audio capture and encoding), the SDK triggers this callback to report the
                current state. This callback indicates the state of the local audio stream, and
                allows you to troubleshoot issues when audio exceptions occur.</p>
            <note id="note" type="attention">When the state is<apiname
                    keyref="LOCAL_AUDIO_STREAM_STATE_FAILED"/> (3), you can view the<parmname>
                    error</parmname> information in the<parmname> error</parmname> parameter.</note>
        </section>
